Periodically refresh ServiceAccount tokens (#205)

Periodically refresh ServiceAccount tokens. This is required to avoid
authentication errors when time-bound tokens [1] are rotated, and the
initially-read token expires. Time bound tokens are beta in Kubernetes
1.21, and GA in 1.22 [2].

[1]: https://github.com/kubernetes/enhancements/tree/master/keps/sig-auth/1205-bound-service-account-tokens
[2]: https://github.com/kubernetes/enhancements/issues/542

Don't use shlex.split on cmd-path (#224)

The code was previously calling shlex.split on cmd-path in addition to cmd-args. If cmd-path had a space in it (which happens on Windows, e.g. C:\Users\<username>\AppData\Local\Google\Cloud SDK\google-cloud-sdk\bin\gcloud.cmd) then shlex.split will split that command line and the command will fail.
